These ported expectations are the authoritative comparison oracle for the caps
document: harbrr must reproduce Jackett's advertised categories, custom-category
ids (e.g. 137107 = BitConverter.ToUInt16(SHA1("con_wii")) + 100000), and
re-derived supportedParams strings (e.g. tv-search dropping imdbid when
AllowTVSearchIMDB is false) on the same definitions.

Divergences from Jackett's serialized form, documented in ../README.md:
  - harbrr emits its own <server title="harbrr"> and uses encoding/xml, which
    renders attribute-only elements as <e></e> rather than Jackett's <e/>;
    both are well-formed and parse identically for Sonarr/Radarr.
  - duplicate-custom-id <category> entries collapse (the mapper de-dups
    advertised categories by id); same-name custom categories tie-break by id.
